# Model routing for the content engine. Copy to monitor/.env.local and fill in.
# monitor/.env.local is gitignored — never commit real credentials.
#
# Out of the box (nothing set), generation uses the `claude` CLI on your logged-in
# plan. Setting all three BULK_* vars adds a degrade path: when the CLI fails
# (e.g. monthly spend limit), generation falls back to this cheaper
# Anthropic-compatible endpoint instead of hard-failing.
#
# BULK_* names on purpose — do NOT export ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL / ANTHROPIC_AUTH_TOKEN
# here: the `claude` CLI honors those and would silently route there too.

# Optional cheap degrade endpoint (any Anthropic-compatible API):
# BULK_BASE_URL="https://your-cheap-endpoint/api/anthropic"
# BULK_AUTH_TOKEN="your-token-here"
# BULK_MODEL="your-cheap-model-id"

# Optional multi-engine failover (opt-in; replaces the CLI→BULK ladder above).
# Requires ~/bin/llm-engine on the machine. It tries plan-a → plan-b → codex → glm
# with per-engine health cooldowns, and makes total failure loud (ops digest) instead
# of silent — built after the 2026-07-06 spend-cap outage. Enable with ONE line in
# monitor/.env.local:
# export GEN_ENGINE_FAILOVER=1
